The National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) has reported that the prices of egg and rice rose in June compared to their market value in May, 2019. The selected food price watch data for June, 2019, analysed by Daily Trust shows that the average price of one dozen of agric eggs (medium size) increased month-on-month by 6.55 per cent to N495.32 in June, 2019, from N464.87 in May, 2019. The report shows that the average price of a piece of agric egg (medium size) per one decreased year-on-year by -5.01 per cent and month-on-month by -8.20 per cent to N39.30 in June, 2019, from N42.82 in May, 2019. Similarly, the average price of 1kg of tomato decreased year-on-year by -28.84 per cent and month-on-month by -9.40 per cent to N226.07 in June, 2019, from N249.52 in May, 2019. The report also reveals that the average price of 1kg of rice (imported high quality sold loose) decreased year-on-year by -5.53 per cent and month-on-month by -2.37 per cent to N352.82 in June, 2019, from N361.39 in May, 2019. The average price of 1kg of yam tubers decreased year-on-year by -36.27 per cent and month-on month by -15.68 per cent to N182.15 in June, 2019, from N216.03 in May, 2019. Prices of egg, tomato, others drop in May – NBS Despite rise in inflation, foodstuff prices fall Inflation down as food prices hit 8-year high – NBS Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin